goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This tells us how many flights are delayed and by how much time. It can help us identify patterns and trends in flight delays.

goals.question: What is the average flight time for different airlines?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of airline vs. average flight time
goals.rationale: This can help us compare the performance of different airlines in terms of flight duration. It can also help us identify which airlines have longer or shorter flights.

goals.question: What is the busiest time of day for flights?
goals.visualization: Line chart of time vs. number of flights
goals.rationale: This can help us identify the peak hours for flight departures and arrivals. It can also help us plan our travel accordingly.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight distances?
goals.rationale: This tells us how far the flights are traveling. It can help us identify which routes are more popular and which airlines are flying longer distances.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight distance and arrival delay?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of distance vs. arrival_delay
goals.rationale: This can help us identify if there is a correlation between flight distance and arrival delay. It can also help us identify outliers and potential causes of delay.

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='departure_delay', bins=50)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    avg_flight_time = data.groupby('airline')['flight_time'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='airline', y='flight_time', data=avg_flight_time)
    plt.title('What is the average flight time for different airlines?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='ignore')
    data['hour'] = data['time'].dt.hour
    hourly_flights = data.groupby('hour').size().reset_index(name='num_flights')
    
    sns.lineplot(x='hour', y='num_flights', data=hourly_flights)
    
    plt.title('What is the busiest time of day for flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
